Sustainable Development Goals

Funnels of inequality

The 2015 SDGs declared that to save the planet no one can be left behind. Recent numbers reveal a different story of inequity-the rich countries have done better at all the SDGs except SDG 12 (Responsible consumption) and SDG 13 (Climate action), in which the developing countries out-perform. This betrays the western narrative of commitment to the SDGs and the reality of unequal growth.
